sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in WellCare Health Plans Inc (Symbol: WCG), where a total volume of 8,826 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 882,600 underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 124.7% of WCG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 707,785 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $260 strike call option expiring April 18, 2019 , with 1,350 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 135,000 underlying shares of WCG.

That number of contracts represents approximately 4.0 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 62.4% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 6.5 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $160 strike call option expiring June 21, 2019 , with 3,753 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 375,300 underlying shares of CRM.

Especially high volume was seen for the $50 strike put option expiring April 18, 2019 , with 26,471 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 2.6 million underlying shares of CVS.
